**Lana Maria Parrilla** (born July 15, 1977) is an American actress. Parrilla
is best known for her roles on television and radio. She was a regular cast
member in the fifth season of the [ABC](/wiki/American_Broadcasting_Company
"American Broadcasting Company") sitcom _[Spin City](/wiki/Spin_City "Spin
City")_ from 2000 to 2001. She later starred in
_[Boomtown](/wiki/Boomtown_\(2002_TV_series\) "Boomtown \(2002 TV series\)")_
(2002-2003), _[Windfall](/wiki/Windfall_\(TV_series\) "Windfall \(TV
series\)")_ (2006), _[Swingtown](/wiki/Swingtown "Swingtown")_ (2008) and as
Doctor Eva Zambrano in the short-lived medical drama _[Miami
Medical](/wiki/Miami_Medical "Miami Medical")_ (2010). She also played the
role of Sarah Gavin during the fourth season of the Fox series
_[24](/wiki/24_\(TV_series\) "24 \(TV series\)")_ in 2005. In 2011, Parrilla
began starring as [The Evil Queen](/wiki/Queen_\(Snow_White\) "Queen \(Snow
White\)")/[Regina Mills](/wiki/Regina_Mills "Regina Mills") in the
[ABC](/wiki/American_Broadcasting_Company "American Broadcasting Company")
fantasy drama series, _[Once Upon a Time](/wiki/Once_Upon_a_Time_\(TV_series\)
"Once Upon a Time \(TV series\)")_. In 2016 Parrilla won a [Teen Choice
Award](/wiki/Teen_Choice_Awards "Teen Choice Awards") for [Choice Sci-
Fi/Fantasy TV
Actress](/wiki/Teen_Choice_Award_for_Choice_TV_Actress_Fantasy/Sci-Fi "Teen
Choice Award for Choice TV Actress Fantasy/Sci-Fi").

## Early
life[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Lana_Parrilla&action=edit&section=1&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro
"Edit section: Early life")]

Parrilla was born in [Brooklyn](/wiki/Brooklyn "Brooklyn"). Her father, [Sam
Parrilla](/wiki/Sam_Parrilla "Sam Parrilla") (1943–94), was a [Puerto
Rican](/wiki/Puerto_Rico "Puerto Rico")-born baseball player who played
professionally for 11 seasons (1963–73), including one season with the [Major
League](/wiki/Major_League_Baseball "Major League Baseball") [Philadelphia
Phillies](/wiki/Philadelphia_Phillies "Philadelphia Phillies") in 1970 as an
outfielder.[1] Her mother is an American painter of [Sicilian](/wiki/Sicily
"Sicily") descent who works in banking. Parrilla has one older sister, Deena,
and a nephew named Sammy.[2] She is also the niece of character actress
[Candice Azzara](/wiki/Candice_Azzara "Candice Azzara"). Parrilla's parents
divorced when she was three years old. She spent her first ten years living
with her mother, and then lived with her father. Lana Parrilla was attacked at
ten years old by a dog, which left her a visible scar on the right side of her
upper lip . During the time she lived with her father, he was too protective
to allow her to attend a performing arts school, which delayed her acting
career.[3] Parrilla lived with her father until his murder in 1994, when she
was 16 and he was 50. Her father was shot once in the chest by a 15-year-old
female assailant at point blank range and later died from the wound.[2][3]
After the death of her father, Parrilla moved in with her mother to [Burbank,
California](/wiki/Burbank,_California "Burbank, California"). Parrilla visited
[Granada](/wiki/Granada "Granada") in 2007 to learn Spanish. After high school
she moved to [Los Angeles](/wiki/Los_Angeles "Los Angeles") and attended
[Beverly Hills Playhouse](/wiki/Beverly_Hills_Playhouse "Beverly Hills
Playhouse") to study acting. She also studied voice for ten years. Parrilla
then began to be cast in small parts and later on, larger ones.

##

###
1999—2010[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Lana_Parrilla&action=edit&section=3&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro
"Edit section: 1999—2010")]

[![](//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/Lana_Parrilla_2012-2.jpg/170px-
Lana_Parrilla_2012-2.jpg)](/wiki/File:Lana_Parrilla_2012-2.jpg)

[](/wiki/File:Lana_Parrilla_2012-2.jpg "Enlarge")

Parrilla in March 2012

In her early career, Parrilla appeared in several movies, including _[Very
Mean Men](/wiki/Very_Mean_Men "Very Mean Men")_ (2000), _Spiders_ (2000), and
_Frozen Stars_ (2003). She made her television debut in 1999, on the UPN
sitcom _[Grown Ups](/wiki/Grown_Ups_\(1999_TV_series\) "Grown Ups \(1999 TV
series\)")_. In 2000, she joined the cast of the ABC comedy series _[Spin
City](/wiki/Spin_City "Spin City")_ , playing Angie Ordonez for one season.
She left the show in 2001. After that she joined [Donnie
Wahlberg](/wiki/Donnie_Wahlberg "Donnie Wahlberg") and [Neal
McDonough](/wiki/Neal_McDonough "Neal McDonough") in the short lived crime
drama _[Boomtown](/wiki/Boomtown_\(2002_TV_series\) "Boomtown \(2002 TV
series\)")_ , for which she received the [Imagen Award](/wiki/Imagen_Award
"Imagen Award") for Best Supporting Actress,[4] for her portrayal of Teresa, a
paramedic. Initially a success, _Boomtown_ began to struggle, and Parrilla's
character became a police academy rookie, to tie her more closely to the rest
of the show. "Boomtown" was cancelled just two episodes into its second
season.

Parrilla guest-starred in a number of television dramas, including
_[JAG](/wiki/JAG_\(TV_series\) "JAG \(TV series\)")_ , _[Six Feet
Under](/wiki/Six_Feet_Under_\(TV_series\) "Six Feet Under \(TV series\)")_ ,
_[Covert Affairs](/wiki/Covert_Affairs "Covert Affairs")_ ,
_[Medium](/wiki/Medium_\(TV_series\) "Medium \(TV series\)")_ , _[The
Defenders](/wiki/The_Defenders_\(2010_TV_series\) "The Defenders \(2010 TV
series\)")_ and _[Chase](/wiki/Chase_\(2010_TV_series\) "Chase \(2010 TV
series\)")_. She had a recurring role in 2004 as Officer Janet Grafton in
_[NYPD Blue](/wiki/NYPD_Blue "NYPD Blue")_. In 2005, Parrilla took a recurring
guest role on the fourth season of the Fox series
_[24](/wiki/24_\(television\) "24 \(television\)")_ as Sarah Gavin, a [Counter
Terrorist Unit](/wiki/Counter_Terrorist_Unit "Counter Terrorist Unit") agent.
After just six episodes, Lana was made a regular cast member; but in the
thirteenth episode, her character was written out after she tried to thwart
another character's promotion from temporary to permanent CTU head [Michelle
Dessler](/wiki/Michelle_Dessler "Michelle Dessler") ([Reiko
Aylesworth](/wiki/Reiko_Aylesworth "Reiko Aylesworth")).

In 2006, Parrilla starred in the [NBC](/wiki/NBC "NBC") summer series
_[Windfall](/wiki/Windfall_\(television_series\) "Windfall \(television
series\)")_ alongside [Luke Perry](/wiki/Luke_Perry "Luke Perry"), fellow
former _24_ cast member [Sarah Wynter](/wiki/Sarah_Wynter "Sarah Wynter"), and
Parilla's former _Boomtown_ castmate [Jason Gedrick](/wiki/Jason_Gedrick
"Jason Gedrick"). In 2007, she guest starred as Greta during the third season
of ABC's _[Lost](/wiki/Lost_\(TV_series\) "Lost \(TV series\)")_ in the
episodes "[Greatest Hits](/wiki/Greatest_Hits_\(Lost\) "Greatest Hits
\(Lost\)")" and "[Through the Looking
Glass](/wiki/Through_the_Looking_Glass_\(Lost\) "Through the Looking Glass
\(Lost\)")" In 2008, she had a leading role on the
[Lifetime](/wiki/Lifetime_\(TV_network\) "Lifetime \(TV network\)") movie _The
Double Life of Eleanor Kendall,_ in which she played Nellie, a divorcee whose
identity has been stolen.[5] Also in 2008, she starred in the [CBS](/wiki/CBS
"CBS") summer series _[Swingtown](/wiki/Swingtown "Swingtown")_ as Trina
Decker, a woman who is part of a [Swinging](/wiki/Swinging_\(sexual_practice\)
"Swinging \(sexual practice\)") couple. In 2010, Parrilla had a female lead
role in the [Jerry Bruckheimer](/wiki/Jerry_Bruckheimer "Jerry
Bruckheimer")-produced _[Miami Medical](/wiki/Miami_Medical "Miami Medical")_
on [CBS](/wiki/CBS "CBS"), which had a short run towards the end of the
2009–10 television season before it was canceled in July 2010.[6] _Windfall_ ,
_Swingtown_ and _Miami Medical_ were all canceled after 13 episodes.

###
2011—present[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Lana_Parrilla&action=edit&section=4&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro
"Edit section: 2011—present")]

[![](//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ce/Lana_Parrilla_2012.jpg/277px-
Lana_Parrilla_2012.jpg)](/wiki/File:Lana_Parrilla_2012.jpg)

[](/wiki/File:Lana_Parrilla_2012.jpg "Enlarge")

Parrilla in 2012

In February 2011, she was cast as Mayor Regina Mills/[The Evil
Queen](/wiki/The_Evil_Queen "The Evil Queen"), in the ABC adventure fantasy
drama pilot, _[Once Upon a Time](/wiki/Once_Upon_a_Time_\(TV_series\) "Once
Upon a Time \(TV series\)")_ created by [Edward Kitsis](/wiki/Edward_Kitsis
"Edward Kitsis") and [Adam Horowitz](/wiki/Adam_Horowitz "Adam Horowitz").[7]
The series debuted in October 2011.[4] The pilot episode was watched by 12.93
million viewers and achieved an adult 18–49 rating/share of 4.0/10 during the
first season, receiving generally favorable reviews from critics.[8]

Parrilla's performance also received positive reviews from critics. In 2012
and 2013, she was regarded as a promising contender for an Emmy Award in the
[Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama
Series](/wiki/Primetime_Emmy_Award_for_Outstanding_Supporting_Actress_in_a_Drama_Series
"Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series")
category,[9][10][11][12][13][14] though she did not receive a nomination. She
won the [TV Guide Award](/wiki/TV_Guide "TV Guide") for Favorite Villain and
the [ALMA Award](/wiki/ALMA_Award "ALMA Award") for Outstanding Actress in a
Drama Series in 2012.[15][16] Parrilla also received a nomination for [Best
Supporting Actress on
Television](/wiki/Saturn_Award_for_Best_Supporting_Actress_on_Television
"Saturn Award for Best Supporting Actress on Television") from the [38th
Saturn Awards](/wiki/38th_Saturn_Awards "38th Saturn Awards").[17]

Parrilla became engaged to boyfriend Fred Di Blasio on April 28, 2013, while
in Israel.[18] The two were married July 5, 2014, shortly before Parrilla
began filming the fourth season of _Once Upon a Time._ [19] Parrilla confirmed
the news on her Twitter account on August 1, 2014.[20]
